main event: A high school student spotted a single oval object over Grand Rapids, Michigan in October 1955.
interesting points: The object was the size of a half dollar held at arm's length, with an indistinct edge and was larger than the object itself.
The witness was taking night photographs at the time of the sighting and snapped 5-6 photos.
The object was at an elevation of 40 degrees and an azimuth of 270 degrees.
No photographs were included in the file.
photographs: No photographs were included in the file
